"title": "1135: God, suffering of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1135: god, suffering of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God suffers on account of the failures and pain of his people, and especially through his Son, Jesus Christ. Scripture often likens God to a parent who suffers pain and grief on account of children.</p>\n<h2>God feels real suffering</h2>\n<h3>He suffers pain because people sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:6\">GEN 6:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:10-1Sam15:11\">1SA 15:10–15:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:35\">1SA 15:35</a></p>\n<h3>He is angered because people sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:58\">PSA 78:58</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:15-Deut32:16\">DEU 32:15–32:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:12-Judg2:13\">JDG 2:12–2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:22\">1KI 21:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek8:17\">EZK 8:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:14\">HOS 12:14</a></p>\n<h2>God identifies with suffering</h2>\n<h3>He suffers with his chosen people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:9\">ISA 63:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:7\">EXO 3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg10:16\">JDG 10:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:15\">2CH 36:15</a></p>\n<h3>He suffers with all humanity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa16:11\">ISA 16:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:31\">JER 48:31</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:15-2Sam24:17\">2SA 24:15–24:17</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:14-1Chr21:17\">1CH 21:14–21:17</a> <em>God suffers even with those who endure punishment from his own hand</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa16:9\">ISA 16:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:32-Jer48:36\">JER 48:32–48:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:8-Hos11:9\">HOS 11:8–11:9</a></p>\n<h3>He suffers as a parent</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:20\">JER 31:20</a></strong> <em>An indication that God suffers in both disciplining and loving.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:14\">ISA 42:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:15\">ISA 49:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:1-Hos11:4\">HOS 11:1–11:4</a></p>\n<h2>God's plan of salvation causes him suffering</h2>\n<h3>He suffered in giving his Son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:32\">ROM 8:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:13-Isa7:14\">ISA 7:13–7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:16\">JHN 3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:25-Rom3:26\">ROM 3:25–3:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:3\">ROM 8:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4\">GAL 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:2\">HEB 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:14\">1JN 4:14</a></p>\n<h3>He suffers because he endures the rejection his Son suffers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:16\">LUK 10:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:4\">1PE 2:4</a></p>\n<h2>God's creation reflects his suffering</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:22\">ROM 8:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:19-Rom8:21\">ROM 8:19–8:21</a></p>\n<h2>God's people share his suffering</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:17\">ROM 8:17</a></strong> <em>There is a sense in which the sufferings of Father and Son are indistinguishable.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:24\">MAT 16:24</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:34\">MRK 8:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:23\">LUK 9:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:22-Matt20:23\">MAT 20:22–20:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:38-Mark10:39\">MRK 10:38–10:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:29\">PHP 1:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:21\">1PE 2:21</a></p>",
